NOVA:  Wait - six whole days?!

53
00:02:30.336 --> 00:02:33.113
VEGA:  Six days - but SI-4 saw the anomaly,

54
00:02:33.113 --> 00:02:35.813
and AU-9 kept the logs of his every

55
00:02:35.813 --> 00:02:38.205
step. He got in. He did not get

56
00:02:38.205 --> 00:02:38.976
out clean.

57
00:02:39.276 --> 00:02:40.754
NULL:  Clean enough... this time.

58
00:02:41.804 --> 00:02:46.160
ARCHIVIST:  Identify, report, and correct system flaws;

59
00:02:47.210 --> 00:02:50.290
VEGA:  Integrity is keeping the system clean and honest.

60
00:02:57.510 --> 00:02:59.895
VEGA:  The Healer's oath. Find the rot, close the

61
00:02:59.895 --> 00:03:01.030
wound, keep it true.

62
00:03:02.080 --> 00:03:04.200
VEGA:  The Firewatch, Incident Response.

63
00:03:04.500 --> 00:03:07.172
VEGA:  When something burns, it sounds the alarm and

64
00:03:07.172 --> 00:03:08.300
contains the blaze.

65
00:03:08.600 --> 00:03:12.988
VEGA:  In reality, that's detecting, reporting, analyzing, containing, and

66
00:03:12.988 --> 00:03:15.280
recovering from security incidents.

67
00:03:16.330 --> 00:03:18.912
NOVA:  When does a threat become an 'incident'?

68
00:03:19.212 --> 00:03:22.171
VEGA:  The moment it stops being hypothetical - malware

69
00:03:22.171 --> 00:03:24.452
